cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CR. 

This paper deals with Bloom filters, a probabilistic data structure commonly used in networking, distributed systems, and databases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of Bloom filters in databases and distributed systems, which makes cs.DB (Databases) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) likely categories as well. The paper also proposes two new data structures, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
